---
title: Number input
---
p.-text
  | Number inputs are used to increase or decrease numeric values, and they require JavaScript to increment and
  | decrement the value when the buttons are pressed. This piece of JavaScripts makes the number increase and decrease
  | when the buttons are pressed and enables and disables the buttons when the number exceeds the min and max limits.

h2 Default
p.-text
  | Call the function chi.numberInput and pass the input element as parameter.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-form__item.-row
      .m-input-number
        input#input-number-1.a-input(type="number", value="0", aria-label="Input label")
        button.a-btn.-icon(aria-label='Decrease')
          .a-btn__content
            i.a-icon
              svg
                use(xlink:href=`#icon-triangle-down`)
        button.a-btn.-icon(aria-label='Increase')
          .a-btn__content
            i.a-icon
              svg
                use(xlink:href=`#icon-triangle-up`)
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-form__item -row">
      <div class="m-input-number">
        <input id="input-number-1" type="number" class="a-input" value="0" aria-label="Input label">
        <button class="a-btn -icon" aria-label="Decrease">
          <div class="a-btn__content">
            <i class="a-icon">
              <svg aria-hidden="true">
                <use xlink:href='#icon-triangle-down'/>
              </svg>
            </i>
          </div>
        </button>
        <button class="a-btn -icon" aria-label="Increase">
          <div class="a-btn__content">
            <i class="a-icon">
              <svg aria-hidden="true">
                <use xlink:href='#icon-triangle-up'/>
              </svg>
            </i>
          </div>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script>chi.numberInput(document.getElementById('input-number-1'));</script>

